                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1254">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.2311/31.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-09T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 9, 1912—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The following telegram has been sent to the Governor of Texas: (See supra.)</p>
                <p>Accordingly you will immediately cancel the permission, pending further
                    instructions, to be based on your report as to a stipulation that the troops
                    will be used exclusively to preserve order at Juárez.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
